HEADWORD: Intra-
<hw>In"tra-</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[L. <ets>intra</ets>, prep.,
within, on the inside; akin to <ets>inter</ets>. See
<er>Inter-</er>.]</ety> <def>A prefix signifying <xex>in</xex>,
<xex>within</xex>, <xex>interior</xex>; <as>as, <ex>intra</ex>ocular,
within the eyeball; <ex>intra</ex>marginal.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Intraaxillary</ent>⟦br⟧
